main event: A round black object was detected by ground radar moving at a high speed in Great Falls, Virginia on 13 October 1957.
interesting points: The object was the size of a pin head's length and was observed for 5-6 seconds., The object was moving along a course of 007 degrees., The observer noted insufficient data for proper evaluation of the sighting., The object traveled rapidly behind trees, making it difficult to see clearly., A separate report noted a round bright orange-red object approximately 30 feet in diameter, also observed in the area.
sighted object: one round black object and one round bright orange-red object
witness description: Names redacted, located approximately one-half mile south of Great Falls near the Potomac River
